      "context": "The hyperbola $g(x)=\\dfrac{a}{x+p}+q$ has asymptotes $x=-1$ and $y=3$, and passes through the point $(0;5)$.",
      "svg": null,
      "archetype": "fun-hyperbola",
      "parts": [
        {
          "q": "Write down the values of $p$ and $q$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "solution": [
            "Vertical asymptote $x=-p=-1$, so $p=1$",
            "Horizontal asymptote $y=q=3$, so $q=3$"
          ],
          "answer": "$p=1$, $q=3$"
        },
        {
          "q": "Show that $a=2$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "solution": [
            "Substitute $(0;5)$: $5=\\dfrac{a}{0+1}+3$",
            "$a=5-3=2$"
          ],
          "answer": "$a=2$"
        },
        {
          "q": "Determine the equation of the axis of symmetry of $g$ that has a negative gradient.",
          "marks": 2,
          "solution": [
            "The symmetry axes pass through the point of intersection of the asymptotes $(-1;3)$",
            "Negative gradient: $y-3=-1(x+1)$",
            "$y=-x+2$"
          ],
          "answer": "$y=-x+2$"
        },
        {
          "q": "Determine the $x$-intercept of $g$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "solution": [
            "$\\dfrac{2}{x+1}+3=0$",
            "$\\dfrac{2}{x+1}=-3\\Rightarrow x+1=-\\dfrac{2}{3}$",
            "$x=-\\dfrac{5}{3}$, so $\\left(-\\dfrac{5}{3};0\\right)$"
          ],
          "answer": "$\\left(-\\dfrac{5}{3};0\\right)$"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "functions-08",
      "difficulty": 2,
      "context": "Given: $f(x)=2x^2-x$",
      "svg": null,
      "archetype": "fun-avg-gradient",
      "parts": [
        {
          "q": "Determine the average gradient of $f$ between $x=-2$ and $x=1$.",
          "marks": 3,
          "solution": [
            "$f(-2)=2(4)-(-2)=10$",
            "$f(1)=2(1)-1=1$",
            "Average gradient $=\\dfrac{1-10}{1-(-2)}=\\dfrac{-9}{3}=-3$"
          ],
          "answer": "$-3$"
        },
        {
          "q": "The average gradient of $f$ between $x=1$ and $x=k$ is $5$. Calculate the value of $k$ (where $k\\neq 1$).",
          "marks": 3,
          "solution": [
            "$\\dfrac{f(k)-f(1)}{k-1}=5$",
            "$\\dfrac{2k^2-k-1}{k-1}=5$",
            "$\\dfrac{(2k+1)(k-1)}{k-1}=5\\Rightarrow 2k+1=5$",
            "$k=2$"
          ],
          "answer": "$k=2$"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "functions-09",
      "difficulty": 1,
      "context": "Given: $f(x)=x^2+3$ and $g(x)=2x+3$",
      "svg": null,
      "archetype": "fun-avg-gradient",
      "parts": [
        {
          "q": "Determine the average gradient of $f$ between $x=0$ and $x=2$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "solution": [
